# 🚀 CODSOFT Web Development Projects

This repository contains the web development projects I completed as part of the CODSOFT Internship Program.  
Each project is crafted using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (for Calculator) to showcase my growing skills in frontend development. 💻

---

## ✅ Projects Included:

### 🧑‍💻 1. Personal Portfolio Website

A clean and responsive personal portfolio website built using **HTML** and **CSS**.  
It presents my skills, background, and projects in a professional layout.

**Features:**
- **Header:** Logo and short tagline
- **About Section:** Profile image and short bio
- **Skills Section:** List of my technical skills
- **Projects Section:** Showcased projects with descriptions and screenshots
- **Resume Section:** Downloadable PDF resume
- **Contact Section:** Email and phone information
- **Footer:** Copyright details

👉 A perfect beginner-friendly project to demonstrate personal branding using just HTML & CSS.

---

### 🎯 2. Landing Page Design

This is a visually appealing **Landing Page** project created using **HTML** and **CSS**.

**Highlights:**
- Organized layout with **sections and columns**
- Use of **CSS for styling, alignment, padding, and color themes**
- Fully responsive and user-friendly
- Encourages creativity and clean design principles

👉 Through this project, I practiced how to structure a real-world landing page and made it stand out aesthetically.

---

### 🧮 3. Basic Calculator

An interactive **Calculator** built using **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**.

**Functionalities:**
- Performs basic arithmetic operations: addition, subtraction, multiplication, division
- User-friendly interface with **CSS Grid** for button alignment
- Dynamic input handling using **JavaScript event listeners**
- Real-time result display with clean logic using **if-else conditions**

👉 This project helped me understand DOM manipulation, logic handling, and interactive UI behavior.

